XIInd or later.

Rectangular shaft. Plundered.
Chamber, square with rounded corners full of sand.
Large number of small mud Ushabtis
Remains of fine painted stucco sarcophagus, on each side of the deceased before 4 gods. Also a boat, probably from the ends. Sarcoph. of Bek en Tahuti
Drawing, Photos 5 & 6
Ivory fragment of wand (?) from the filling of the shaft.
B.2. had a N. chamber plundered from B.1. The shaft descended further but not finished.

Cemetery: Near the house
Tomb: B.10.
Plundered.
Apparently a single barrel-vaulted chamber, gebel floor. [See over] The burials badly disturbed, 5 skulls found, one mummified.
Small fragt. of papyrus, small plain wooden hawk with flat base, fragt. of larger one of painted stucco. 
One large biconical carnelian bead & numerous smaller beads
Two small pendants of dark green stone viz. [drawing] broken, & [drawing] scaraboid
A few fragments of sarcophagus, broken Ushabtis etc & a piece of worked limestone from the rubbish above & near the vault.

Sarcoph. frags.

Cemetery: Near house
Tomb: B.11.
Plundered
Rectangular shaft. N.W - S.E
In shaft 2 vases [drawing], broken & Ushabti fragments; a few bits of a thin leather object.
In shaft were found later the horn (broken) & part of skull of a large animal, mummified animal limbs & human skulls.
There was a North chamber broken into from B.10. The shaft then descended further but there was no second chamber.
Head of animal (? dog) in shaft. 
A paw prob. of this animal was found over B.10., & indeed the fillings of these two are very mixed.

Tomb: B.11
Rectangular shaft. NW-SE.
In shaft 2 vases, broken & Ushabti fragments; a few bits of a thin leather object. In shaft were found later the horn (broken) & part of skull of a large animal. Mummified animal limbs & human skulls.

Cemetery: near house
Tomb: B.12
Rectangular shaft.
In top of shaft many vases & frag'ts.
a) 9 vases
b) one vase & a second smaller
c) 13 small limps of mud
d) 7 large reddish vases

Lower down, at the entrance to & in South chamber was found the material given over page. The box was just inside chamber. 
Chamber 250 x 120 x 134 (cm) deep.
Three pots from the top of shaft.
-black bands on pink; broken; & 1 small Ushabti.

In & at entrace of S chamber:
a) large masses of pottery fragments.
b) small dab of mud
c) Box of ivory & wood inlaid in alternate rows on thick wood.
d) Large alab. kohl pot 69 diam., blue gl. lid
e) Small alab. kohl pot, lid to fit, height 45 mm
f) Broken alab. kohl pot lid.
g) Three v. large hollow bl. glaze beads.
h) Green gl. scarab 16 mm long.
j) V. small blue gl. Bes figure.
k) A date stone
l) Two bl. glaze beads
m) Piece of wood, prob. end of mirror handle
n) Wooden kohl-stick
o) Thick ivory bracelet
p) Fragments of leaves & 2 nuts
q) Fragments of leather.

Cemetery: B
Tomb: B.12 (cont)
r) 12 more vases
s) 5 good red ware basins
t) 4 pink ware dishes with white paint
u) Stucco fragment (painted)
v) Pieces of cloth
w) 12 vases, small, red ware, two with black rims
x) Two round wooden objects, probably legs for the box.

North Chamber 200 x  80 x 70 cm:
Two bodies, girl in coffin to West with 25 scarabs around her. Boy to East, skeleton badly disturbed, skull broken in corner. Two thigh bones of a man also. Large number of vases, in & outside chamber.
a) Twenty-five scarabs. 22 in chamber.
b) Hollow bracelet of bronze.
c) Piece of a horn.
d) Alab. kohl vase & lid 61 mm high, in chamb.
e) Alab. vase, 80 mm.
f) Grey stone kohl vase 27 mm high.
j) Small piece of lid for e).
k) Vases of earthenware:
    1. large vase, A
     2. large [...] 13
     18 type C
      4 type D
       2 smaller basins

Cemetery: B, near house
Tomb: B.13
Rectangular shaft beside B.12.
Two chambers to N, one to S.
From just outside S chamber [B.13, c, mark]
a) Two large inscribed Ushabtis of stone  [Drawing of inscription]
b) A yellow pebble.
c) Frag't. of black pottery vase.
d) Frag't. of sarcophagus.
The shaft decrease & there was a cutting in its east side just below the level of the lower chambers. (see over)
[Several small vases in top of shaft, sic in all & two cakes of clay]
Marked B.13.d.

Yellow hieroglyphs on black ground.
In the east cutting a burial of a woman in a totally destroyed coffin of wood & painted stucco. Body on left side & extended [Objects B.13.a]
a) Alab. kohl vase & kohl sick under head.
b) Bl. gl. scarab above left wrist.
c) Alab. vase with scalloped top at left hand.
d) Alab. vase at left ankle.
e) Ear of stucco at head.

In the shaft just outside this burial, which was [...] with large bricks were found [B.13.b]:
a) White incised vase in fragments.
b) Thin red ware bowl.
c) Broken Kush of white clay.
d) Fragments of rough vase with wavy line decoration.
e) Pieces of 4 other vases.
f) An inlaid eye, & 6 amethyst beads.

Cemetery: B, near house
Tomb: B.13. cont.
The cave in East side extended north & contained a fine wooden coffin, now rotted. In this was a body with no furniture. The lid of the coffin had been raised by the plunderers.

South Chamber:
This was entirely empty. See plan.
Outer chamber: 225 x 165 x 102 deep.
Inner chamber: 210 x 80 x 95 deep.
Canopic pit: 60 x 35 x 38
& 55 cm from SE end of chamber.
Over

North Chamber:
1. Upper: Two bowls of 13th. Dyn. type, one with red lattice pattern. Mark B.13.f.
Large granite arm.

2. Lower: no finds.

Cemetery: B, near house
Tomb: B.14
Rectangular shaft NW of B.12 & about 5 m distant.
Twp chambers N & S rather near top.
The filling gave long blue bl. beads.
Outside S chamber & just at entrance:
a) Small piece of wood.
b) Small bl. gl. Ushabti.
c) Long bl. gl. beads.

Two chambers N & S much deeper, in N were:
a) two beads.
b) Piece of transparent brown stone.
c) Bl. gl. amulet.
d) Piece of vase.

Cemetery: near house
Tomb: B.15
Rectangular broad shaft, 2 chambers:
In the shaft, 2 alab. frag'ts., bl. gl. frag'ts.
Shell & Ushabti fragments.
Broken painted vase type XVIVth.

In S Chamber:
a) frag'ts. of painted stucco sarcoph.
b) Rough fragments of leather.
c) Small vase, whitish colour.

In N chamber:
a) Black stone kohl vase & lid 55 mm.

Cemetery: B
Tomb: B.16
Rectangular shaft.
Carnel. & bl. gl. beads in shaft.

Tomb: B.17
Rect. shaft south of B.15.
North chamber, broken [...], contained.
a) Alab. kohl vase, broken & re[...] with new lid.
b) Ivory dagger handle.
c) Bronze needle, broken.
d) Two silver earrings.
e) Shells, beads, frag'ts. of wood.
f) Disc of alab.
g) Fragment of schist.
h) White shell beads.
i) Frag't. of alab. kohl vase.
k) Ushabti fragments.
l) Two red vases.
                             OVER

In the floor of the N chamber lay a female body in sarcophagus of wood. Hair long, supine, few carnel. & bl. gl. beads.
Outside chamber in shaft lay a coffin with lid beside it. Plundered, bones disturbed, female(?), no furniture.

Tomb: B.20
Turba N & S;  2.5 x 1 x 2.90
